@node OS3 "The OS3 Preview version"
The OS3 Preview is an experimental version of PPMtoSCR using the colour
mapping routines built in to OS3.

OS3P attempts to map pictures to the closest colours in the Spectrum's
palette (currently I am using the ZX Datatype's colour palette)

In theory, this should give much better results than my current routine. 
However, it seems to map rather too many colours to white.

Please try converting pictures with this version, and @{"let me know" link contact} how much
success you have.

Some pictures do look good using the OS3 routines, but I think I need to
adjust the colour map quite a lot.  If anybody has a colour palette which
will produce better results, then please @{"let me know" link contact}.

If you want to convert SCRs into TAPs or whatever, then the OS3 version does
a better job than the original...

@{b}Limitations@{ub}

All colour mapping adjustment features are not implemented.  ie. GREYSCALE
NOBRIGHT, COLOURSENSE, BRIGHTSENSE and WHITESENSE will do nothing.

It is slower than the original
@endnode

